The paper discusses mobile security and proposes an adaptive neuro-fuzzy inference system (ANFIS) for implicit authentication. This system involves behavioral data collected from Android users, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of ANFIS also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of traditional security measures, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobile devices, which can also fall under the category of mobile computing and applications (cs.MA) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). However, since the focus is on security and authentication, the aforementioned categories are more likely.
